tively navigate resettlement processes in pursuit of their own benefit. However, their resistance is limited by varied forms of state-backed infrastructural violence. Through extensive fieldwork with scientists, urban planners, and everyday citizens in southwestern China, Ecological States exposes the ways in which the scientific logics and practices fundamental to China's green urbanization have solidified state power and contributed to dispossession and social inequalityWith support from the Henry Luce Foundation, our goal is to produce all titles in this series both in Open Access, for reasons of global accessibility and equity, as well as in print editions.  afunded by Luce Foundation  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aEnvironmental History. 4aGEOGRAPHY-PHYSICAL & CULTURAL. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Asian Studies.2bisacsh  asustainable urbanization in China, urban-rural inequality in China, nature conservation in China, China's rural transformation, ecological civilizations, environmental governance, ecological policies in China, geography.1 aPark, Albert L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb2 aLuce Foundationefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKA